<Link id="l00160" /><CodeLine lineNumber="160"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Support class for static dtor execution. For hosted (in-process) JITs</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00161" /><CodeLine lineNumber="161"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///        only!</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00162" /><CodeLine lineNumber="162"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00163" /><CodeLine lineNumber="163"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   If a &#95;&#95;cxa&#95;atexit function isn&#39;t found C++ programs that use static</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00164" /><CodeLine lineNumber="164"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// destructors will fail to link. However, we don&#39;t want to use the host</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00165" /><CodeLine lineNumber="165"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// process&#39;s &#95;&#95;cxa&#95;atexit, because it will schedule JIT&#39;d destructors to run</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00166" /><CodeLine lineNumber="166"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// after the JIT has been torn down, which is no good. This class makes it easy</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00167" /><CodeLine lineNumber="167"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// to override &#95;&#95;cxa&#95;atexit (and the related &#95;&#95;dso&#95;handle).</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="171"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// inside the JIT, but before searching the host process&#39;s symbol table. When</span></CodeLine>
